1
00:01:58,960 --> 00:01:59,915
Hello?

2
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,838
I have a collect call
from Wayne Felde...

3
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:04,270
...a death-row inmate at
the correctional facility.

4
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:07,517
- Will you accept the charges?
- Hold on.

5
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:09,756
Why am I in your bed?

6
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:13,391
Go back to sleep. Go back to sleep.

7
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:15,593
Will you accept the charges?

8
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:18,314
- Hold on, just a second.
- Ma'am?

9
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:21,554
Ma'am, will you accept
the charges?

10
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:25,074
- Ma'am?
- Yes, I'll accept the charges.

11
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:26,235
Go ahead.

12
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:29,714
- You didn't wanna talk to me.
- No, it's not that.

13
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:31,315
I didn't get much sleep.

14
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:33,829
Yeah. I didn't get me much either.

15
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:38,670
Just had me a fine meal
of fried chicken and gravy.

16
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:41,910
That's what everybody wants
for their last meal.

17
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,074
Don't be sad, girl.

18
00:02:45,640 --> 00:02:47,631
I'm getting what I want.

19
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:48,989
It's what I deserve.

20
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:53,236
I am glad
I had the chance to know you, Wayne.

21
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:56,918
Time's up.

22
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:00,393
Well...

23
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:05,638
...I better go now.

24
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:08,229
I got some place I gotta be.

25
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:11,317
You tak e care, darling.

26
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:42,238
- Graves Thomas.
- Good morning, Prissy.

27
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:44,112
- Why'd you do that?
- Do what?

28
00:03:44,320 --> 00:03:46,788
Let me give my home number
to Wayne Felde.

29
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,468
- He called you?
- Yep.

30
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:51,751
- Are you all right?
- Yep.

31
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:56,713
Well, he was guilty anyway, darling.

32
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:59,036
He even admitted it himself.

33
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:01,715
And you was the only one
kept trying to help him.

34
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:03,512
Obviously didn't help him enough.

35
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:06,280
You don't know that.

36
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:13,552
What's this?

37
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:16,672
- Why is this case back on my desk?
- Do you know Calvin Willis?

38
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:18,518
I thought you said
he was a lost cause.

39
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:20,233
Was a lost cause.

40
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:24,035
Now, I got the detective coming in that
worked on the case for a little chat.

41
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:26,913
Well, I'm officially resigning
as a babysitter to the doomed.

42
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:30,999
Thing about old Calvin here, though,
he might actually be innocent.

43
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:33,515
- Right.
- No, I'm telling you, darling.

44
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:36,837
You don't need a law degree or cane
pole to smell something fishy here.

45
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:39,190
You remember
that detective I mentioned?

46
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:42,517
She was a metre maid about
the time the city council decided...

47
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:45,115
...that the old boys needed
more women on the force.

48
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:49,313
So they call in Miss Loretta Brooks,
give her a badge, give her a gun...

49
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:51,954
...and tell her to go to work
on this child-rape case...

50
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:54,351
...involving an 11 -year-old girl.

51
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,959
Her first case.

52
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:58,276
Right out of the chute,
no experience whatsoever.

53
00:04:58,480 --> 00:05:01,233
Hey, I don't know how innocent he is,
but that man ain't guilty.

54
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:04,113
I don't wanna work on a rape case.
This one's with a child.

55
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:05,878
And a man that's wrongly accused...

56
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:08,435
...given a life sentence,
without a chance for parole.

57
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:10,870
Well, if he's innocent,
you'll get him out.

58
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:13,230
You do know
there are other paralegals in town...

59
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:14,953
...don't you, Miss Prissy?

60
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:18,038
None as smart and as cheap,
Mr. Graves.

61
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:20,758
Well, that's true.

62
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,718
Here's daddy.

63
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:30,036
- Daddy!
- Daddy!

64
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:31,468
Give me some sugar.

65
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:32,669
Hey, darling.

66
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:34,359
Hey, baby.

67
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:35,959
- I love you, Mama.
- I love you.

68
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:37,479
Thanks for coming.

69
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:38,795
Hey, baby.

70
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,479
Baby.

71
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:42,108
I missed you so much.

72
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,269
I want that candy.

73
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:46,994
No, no, no. Share.
You got to share, now.

74
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:49,111
Why Papa didn't come?

75
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:52,273
He wasn't feeling up to it today.

76
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:55,952
He said I should give you a kiss
for him.

77
00:05:57,640 --> 00:06:00,074
Just losing strength, Calvin.

78
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:01,713
Just losing strength.

79
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:04,793
Willis.

80
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:07,388
Move away from her.

81
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,033
That's my wife, man.

82
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:12,950
I don't care if it's your dying mama.

83
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:15,310
You keep your distance,
or the visit is over.

84
00:06:15,520 --> 00:06:18,637
You can't tell me
I can't touch my own husband.

85
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:21,115
Visit's over.
Escort these folks out of here.

86
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:22,309
Come on, man.

87
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:24,750
What are you talking about?
I just got here.

88
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:27,155
I just got here.
What are you talking about?

89
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:30,712
You don't have the right to keep me
from seeing my own husband.

90
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:33,270
- Michelle.
- Get off of me.

91
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:35,630
It's all right, baby. They in a rush.

92
00:06:43,160 --> 00:06:46,038
Hi, this us. Leave a message.

93
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:48,117
Prissy, please pick up. It's Margie.

94
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:50,151
Something happened
down at the lak e today.

95
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:52,157
Graves and I were on the boat.

96
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:55,352
I can't believe
y'all took the boat out anyway.

97
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:58,358
I thought Graves was like a cat,
didn't wanna get his hair wet.

98
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:01,472
He's dead. He's dead, Prissy.

99
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:04,399
Lightning, and he got struck down.

100
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,831
And he's dead.

101
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:09,235
Is this for real?

102
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,754
Yes.

103
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:13,110
- The storm. The storm...
- Oh, my God.

104
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:16,278
...and lightning struck him.

105
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:18,831
- Mama?
- Oh, that's awful.

106
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:21,713
I don't know what to do.

107
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:25,873
I don't know.

108
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:36,113
Hey, Prissy.

109
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:37,753
Hey, Reynolds.

110
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:41,111
I can't tell you how sorry I am
about Graves Thomas.

111
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,639
I don't know how many times
I heard the man say:

112
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:47,070
"If I am lying,
may I be struck by lightning...

113
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:48,429
...by the Lord Almighty."

114
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:52,431
Must have been one big-ass lie
he told on that boat.

115
00:07:57,600 --> 00:08:00,478
Well, he sure thought the world
of you.

116
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:06,515
Always boasted you could out-brief
any attorney in town.

117
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:09,074
You know, Prissy...

118
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:11,953
...I could use a top-shelf paralegal
in my office.

119
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:14,594
The job's yours if you want it.

120
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,230
I might have to take you up on that.

121
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:20,438
You're?

122
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:22,873
You wanna come in with me?

123
00:08:23,080 --> 00:08:26,516
No, this is as close as I wanna get
to another coffin.

124
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:30,671
When you get ready to go back
to work, you come by my office.

125
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:32,677
Thank you.
I might need a day or so.

126
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:33,995
Okay.

127
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:51,433
Look.

128
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:55,511
Hey, who are you?

129
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:57,592
What you doing here?

130
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:58,994
- Well...
- Keisha.

131
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:01,919
Child, haven't I told you
a thousand times...

132
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:05,510
...any talking to strangers need doing,
you come get Granny?

133
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:09,190
Are you Calvin Willis' grandmother?

134
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:11,994
Whatever you have to say
about my Calvin...

135
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:14,475
...I hope you don't say it
in front of his children.

136
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:17,319
I'm Prissy Gregory.
I'm from Graves Thomas' office.

137
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:19,954
Oh, you Mr. Thomas' girl.

138
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:21,798
He told us all about you.

139
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,434
Told us about
how you was playing with a gun...

140
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:26,596
...and shot yourself in the leg.

141
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:29,792
Boy, that story made
a great impression on my grand.

142
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,956
Now, y'all run on over there
to play now.

143
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:33,878
Your mama be on directly.

144
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:36,517
Come on in.

145
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:41,555
I can't say as I understand
why God take him that way.

146
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:44,115
Lord know more than me.

147
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:46,914
- Afternoon, Mama.
- Michelle.

148
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:49,554
- How you feeling, Papa?
- I'm okay.

149
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:51,318
This here is Prissy Gregory.

150
00:09:51,520 --> 00:09:53,909
- She works with Mr. Thomas.
- Hi. Hi.

151
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:57,829
Michelle is Calvin's wife.
She's just like my own daughter.

152
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:02,319
Prissy just told us
that Mr. Thomas passed last week.

153
00:10:03,640 --> 00:10:06,677
I brought Calvin's case file.

154
00:10:07,520 --> 00:10:09,875
I know Mr. Thomas was only on this
a few months...

155
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:12,674
...but he'd gone through
your retainer.

156
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:17,908
Unfortunately, I don't know of a lawyer
who would do the case pro bono.

157
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:20,031
I'll take care of it.

158
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:24,149
Child, please,
how you gonna take care of it?

159
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:27,079
All right, now, Mama, you
got enough on your plate already.

160
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:31,276
Thank you for coming.

161
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:40,471
Hey. You shouldn't have come here.

162
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:42,113
You should've called me.

163
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:44,595
I thought it was Mr. And Ms. Newton
who hired Graves.

164
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:46,677
They was. They gave him
every cent they had.

165
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:48,677
Now all they got
is heartache and worries.

166
00:10:48,880 --> 00:10:50,359
That woman in there raised Calvin.

167
00:10:50,560 --> 00:10:52,437
More of a mother
than the one that left him.

168
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:54,870
His granddad,
you see him eaten away with cancer.

169
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:59,313
And you come here carrying this
burden they can't do nothing about?

170
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:00,509
Shame on you.

171
00:11:01,320 --> 00:11:03,311
I was just doing my job,
and I didn't know.

172
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:04,714
No, I don't suppose you did.

173
00:11:04,920 --> 00:11:07,434
Don't suppose you got any idea
what it's like...

174
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:11,189
...to have the one you love most
taken from you for no reason at all.

175
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:14,870
Keisha, Booji, come on,
it's time to go home.

176
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:17,717
Hey, listen, I'm sorry.

177
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:21,831
I'm sorry.
Why don't you give me the file back?

178
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:24,759
And I'll do what I can
to get you a good lawyer.

179
00:11:31,040 --> 00:11:33,634
Fine. I won't hold my breath.

180
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,068
No, don't.

181
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:37,316
If I do find you one,
you need to be ready...

182
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:41,115
...to go through everything
about this case all over again.

183
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,349
Would you tell your boss...

184
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:49,074
...Graves Thomas
left him a little something in his will?

185
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:51,991
No, but if I tell him
it's a pro-bono case...

186
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:54,077
...he won't call me back, will he?

187
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:57,799
Okay.

188
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:03,558
- Hello?
- I'm here to see Graves Thomas.

189
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:05,830
Oh, I'm sorry.
I thought I'd cancelled all...

190
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:08,076
No, I told him not to write it down.

191
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:09,998
Look, if he's not here,
it's fine by me.

192
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:12,077
No, wait a minute. Who are you?

193
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:15,113
- Loretta Brooks.
- The detective on the Willis case?

194
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:19,199
You know, I am so tired of having to
defend that damn police photo line-up.

195
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:21,630
Just because I didn't know
to keep a record...

196
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:24,400
...of how it was assembled,
doesn't mean it wasn't legit.

197
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:27,956
It's not like I put pictures of white guys
in there. They were all black.

198
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:29,878
That girl pointed at Willis, all right?

199
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,438
I don't know
what you're talking about.

200
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:34,551
Graves won't be working
on the Willis case.

201
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:37,558
Then what the hell am I doing here?

202
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:17,397
Hi. Are you Jo Anne Johnson?

203
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:20,672
Reggie send you down here?
Lady, I ain't got his money.

204
00:13:20,880 --> 00:13:23,235
No, no, no,
I'm not here about money.

205
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,795
I wanted to ask you
about your daughter Lucretia.

206
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:27,598
What business you got
asking about her?

207
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:30,519
- Can I come in?
- No, Lucretia don't live here no more.

208
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:34,110
- She lives with your sister in Ohio?
- How you know that? You police?

209
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:37,551
No, I'm a paralegal.
And I'm just helping out on the case.

210
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:39,478
I've been reading
the trial transcripts.

211
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:41,511
There are things
that I don't understand.

212
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:45,554
Like how come you identified
Calvin Willis...

213
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:47,398
...as your daughter's attacker...

214
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:49,670
...when you weren't actually home
that night?

215
00:13:49,880 --> 00:13:51,598
- I ain't got time for this.
- No, please.

216
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:55,395
I just need to know, why did
you give the detective Calvin's name...

217
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:57,158
...before she started investigating?

218
00:13:57,360 --> 00:13:59,874
Because Chante saw his car
parked outside my house.

219
00:14:00,080 --> 00:14:02,548
Right, but did Lucretia
know Calvin too?

220
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:04,950
She picked his picture
out of a photo line-up.

221
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:07,958
But she couldn't identify him
in court, right?

222
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:12,110
Now, I understand that Lucretia
was a special-education child.

223
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:15,118
And that means
that she couldn't qualify as a witness...

224
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:17,709
...to give testimony in court.

225
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:21,876
When your baby girl look at you...

226
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:25,152
...her face swollen up, bleeding,
half her teeth gone...

227
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:27,715
...and point to a man...

228
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:30,311
...you believe her.

229
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:05,799
Hey. Listen,
I still haven't found you a lawyer yet.

230
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:08,116
I had hoped
that I could help you myself.

231
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:11,392
But this case, it's just like...
It's riddled with holes.

232
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:13,352
It's just that...

233
00:15:13,560 --> 00:15:16,438
I'm just really not the right person.

234
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:18,559
What happened?

235
00:15:18,760 --> 00:15:21,035
Papa died.

236
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:17,679
Calvin.

237
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:23,276
- Daddy, Daddy.
- Hi, Booji.

238
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:53,792
- Mama.
- Baby.

239
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:01,193
This is Miss Prissy.

240
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:03,789
She made it
so you could be here today.

241
00:17:04,320 --> 00:17:05,992
Hey.

242
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:10,231
What you go and do that for?

243
00:17:11,120 --> 00:17:12,314
Calvin.

244
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:14,112
Who are you to me or my papa?

245
00:17:15,840 --> 00:17:18,115
This ain't the day
for you to forget your manners.

246
00:17:18,320 --> 00:17:19,469
You thank this woman.

247
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:21,989
